The paper deals with plan recognition, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of vector representations of actions is a common technique in natural language processing (cs.CL) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the limitations of traditional plan recognition approaches, which could fall under the category of computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) or software engineering (cs.SE).
